8.
How
to Contact Us
1.
Categories and Sources of
Personal Information
We collect the following types
of information through your use of the Ford DiagNow
app
when connected via the Vehicle Communication Module (“
VCM
”) Lite device to
the vehicle
:
Information You Provide.
When
you use the Ford DiagNow
app
, you will be asked or given the option to provide information
to us, such as
:
·
Security:
the credentials (username and password) provided
to you for your Ford service account (which you may have created through
MotorCraftService.com), which are required to log into this app.
·
Preferences:
your preferred measurement system (imperial
or metric) and the appearance theme for the app can be changed in your Profile.
The default measurement system is metric, and the default appearance theme is
“Light.”
Information From Your Mobile
Device.
We automatically collect some information from your mobile
device when you use the Ford DiagNow app:
·
Digital Activity:
we collect information about
how you use the app, such as which features are used, how often they are used,
the steps you use in your diagnostic activities, and whether the activity was
successfully completed. This information is connected to your username or a
unique app identifier we generate (see below).
Note
for Android devices only:
the Android operating system on the
mobile device requires location services to be enabled in order to connect to
Bluetooth devices. To connect via Bluetooth to the VCM Lite, Android mobile
devices need to enable location services. Neither the Ford DiagNow app nor Ford
collects mobile device location.
Information From a Vehicle.
If the
vehicle you are working on belongs to you, the Ford DiagNow app may collect the
following data when the VCM Lite is connected to the vehicle and you run functions
or interrogate modules to review the following:
·
Vehicle Data:
information about the status,
performance, and diagnostics of the vehicle and its systems, parts, and
components, such as odometer, tire pressure, fluid levels, and diagnostic codes.
·
Driving Data:
information about how the
vehicle is operated and used (such as speed, use of accelerator, brakes,
steering, and engine RPM, etc.).
·
Vehicle Location:
the precise GPS location of
the vehicle.
This
data will be linked to the vehicle’s unique identification number (“VIN”), your
username, and a unique app identifier we generate (see below).
If the vehicle you are working
on belongs to someone other than you, the information collected from the
vehicle via the Ford DiagNow app is to be used only for vehicle diagnostics,
service, or repair unless you obtain their consent to use it for other purposes.
Information We Generate About
You.
We generate new information from the data we collect. For
example:
·
Identifiers We Generate:
we may generate unique
identifiers associated with your Ford service account username (which you use
to log in) or with your Ford DiagNow app usage sessions. The unique identifiers
help us identify you or associate the information generated through your use of
the app to you.
2.
Our Use of Personal Information
We use the personal information
collected in connection with your
use of the Ford DiagNow app as
follows
:
Purposes of Use
Categories of Personal Information
Product and Service Delivery
. To provide the
  features and services of the app,
updating the app, troubleshooting,
  and
providing and technical support.
Security, Preferences, Digital Activity, Device and Mobile
  Location, Vehicle Data, Driving Data, Vehicle Location, Identifiers We
  Generate
Product Improvement
. To improve the app and
  other tools for vehicle diagnostics, service, and repair.
Preferences, Digital Activity, Vehicle Data, Driving Data,
  Vehicle Location, Identifiers We Generate
Research and Development
. To conduct research
  and develop new products, services, and tools for vehicle diagnostics,
  service, and repair.
Preferences, Digital Activity, Vehicle Data, Driving Data,
  Vehicle Location, Identifiers We Generate
Marketing and Advertising
. To promote the app and
  other tools for vehicle diagnostics, service, and repair.
Preferences, Digital Activity, Vehicle Data, Identifiers We
  Generate
Business Operations
. To operate our business
  and perform business functions such as accounting, finance, tax, regulatory
  compliance, litigation, information security, privacy, fraud detection and
  prevention, protection of our rights and property, supplier and vendor
  management, human resources, information technology, and improving our
  internal operations.
Security, Preferences, Digital Activity, Device and Mobile
  Location, Vehicle Data, Identifiers We Generate
Support for Laws, Property, Safety, and Exigent Circumstances
. To
  support our compliance with valid inquiries and directives from law
  enforcement or other government agencies; to
act under exigent
  circumstances to help prevent the loss of life or serious injury or to
  protect the personal safety of Ford or affiliate personnel, users of our
  vehicles, websites, or mobile apps, our visitors, or the public; and to
  protect the rights or property of others.
Security, Preferences, Digital Activity, Device and Mobile
  Location, Vehicle Data, Vehicle Location, Identifiers We Generate
In carrying out these
purposes, we may combine personal information we collect in connection with
your use of
the Ford DiagNow app
with information that we have
collected through other diagnostic tools that worked on the same vehicle(s) you
work on, including tools used by others.
Finally, we may de-identify
information we collect through your use of the app and use it for any purpose
in accordance with applicable law.
3.
Our
Sharing of Personal Information
We share
the personal information collected in connection with your
use of
the Ford DiagNow app
with your consent, when you direct us to share it with others,
as necessary to complete your transactions, or to provide the products,
features, services, or experiences you have requested or authorized. In
addition:
Dealers:
if you work
     for a Ford or Lincoln dealer, we share information about the diagnostic
     and service events generated through your use of the app with that dealer.
Affiliates:
we share the personal
     information collected in connection
with your
use of the app
among the
     companies within the Ford Motor Company family of companies and
     affiliates.
Our
     “family of companies” is the group of companies related to us by common
     control or ownership. Information is shared within this “family” as a
     normal part of conducting business operations and offering products,
     features, and services to our customers.
Service Providers, Suppliers, and
     Agents:
we
     may share the personal information collected in connection
with your
use of the app
with
our vendors,
     suppliers, service providers, contractors, and agents (including our
     affiliates acting in this capacity) (“
Suppliers
”) working on our
     behalf for the purposes described in this Policy. We require them to use
     it only to perform that work for us and to use adequate safeguards to protect
     the confidentiality of the personal information they receive. For example,
     companies we've hired to provide customer service or technical support, or
     to support some of the features in the app, may need the personal
     information to provide those functions. Reasonable contractual or other
     measures we may take to protect your personal information while processed
     or handled by Suppliers are subject to legal requirements in the United
     States, Canada, and other foreign countries (for example, lawful
     requirements to disclose personal information to governmental authorities
     in those countries).
Law Enforcement Agencies, Courts,
     Regulatory Agencies, and Others:
we will share the personal information
     collected in connection
with your
use of the app
when we
     believe that doing so is necessary to:
comply with applicable law or respond
      to valid legal process, including from law enforcement or other
      government agencies;
act under exigent circumstances to help
      prevent the loss of life or serious injury or to protect the personal
      safety of Ford or affiliate personnel, users of our vehicles, websites, or
      mobile apps, our visitors, or the public;
detect, investigate, prevent, or
      otherwise address fraud or privacy issues;
operate and maintain the security of
      our products, including to detect, investigate, prevent, stop, or
      remediate an attack on our computer systems or networks; or
protect the rights or property of
      ourselves, our affiliates, or others, including by enforcing our
      agreements, terms, and policies.
Parties to Corporate Transactions:
we may also share
     the personal information collected in connection
with your
use of the app
as part of a
     corporate transaction or proceeding such as a merger, financing,
     acquisition, bankruptcy, dissolution, or at transfer, divestiture, or sale
     of all or a portion of our business or assets.
Finally, we may share de-identified information in accordance
with applicable law.
4.
Integration with Other
Services
The Ford DiagNow app may
integrate with, or contain
links to, other products, services, features, websites, mobile apps, platforms,
or properties that Ford owns or operates and that display or refer to their own
privacy policies (“
Other Ford Services
”). Those privacy policies apply
to the Other Ford Services, but this Policy does not.
5.
Security
and Retention of Your Personal Information
Safeguarding personal information is important to us. While no systems,
applications, or websites are 100% secure, we take reasonable and appropriate
steps to help protect personal information from unauthorized access, use,
disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
To help us protect personal information, we request that you use
a strong password for your Ford service account and never share it with anyone
or use the same password with other mobile apps, websites, or accounts.
6.
California
Privacy Rights
This section describes the rights that the California Consumer
Privacy Act of 2018 (“CCPA”) gives to California residents under Cal. Civ. Code
§
1798.145(n).
Please be aware that Ford and Lincoln dealers and independent
repair facilities (“
IRF
”) are separate legal entities from Ford Motor Company and,
under the CCPA, separate businesses from Ford Motor Company. If you want to
exercise your CCPA rights regarding personal information a dealer or IRF may
have collected about you, you must contact the dealer or IRF directly and
exercise your rights through them.
Right to Opt Out of Sales.
This Privacy Policy describes above how we share personal
information with others in the context of your use of
the Ford
DiagNow app
. If you are a Ford or Lincoln vehicle owner, or if you use our
websites, mobile apps, or other products or services for your personal or
household use, our Ford US privacy policy at
https://www.ford.com/help/privacy/
describes
how we share personal information with others in those contexts.
Under the CCPA, some of this sharing is considered a
"sale" even if we do not receive money in exchange for the
information we share.
You have the right to instruct us to stop the kind of sharing
that the CCPA treats as "sales," and not to engage in that kind of
sharing in the future, unless you choose to allow it. Your instruction to stop
"selling" personal information about you will not affect “sales” that
occurred before you gave us the instruction.
Please be aware that there may be circumstances where we can
continue to share personal information about you with others, as permitted by
the CCPA. These circumstances may include carrying out previous directions
you've given us to disclose personal information about you to others or sharing
personal information about you with our service providers so that they can
provide services to us.
You can exercise your right to opt-out from future sales of
personal information in the following ways:
·
By clicking this link:
Do Not Sell My
Personal Information
and completing the webform; or
·
By calling us, toll-free, at 1-888-459-1291, Monday through
Friday from 5:00 am until 8:00 pm Pacific time or Saturday from 5:00 am until
5:00 pm Pacific time. Our call center will be closed on Sundays and on New
Year’s Day, Memorial Day, Independence Day, Labor Day, Thanksgiving Day, the
day after Thanksgiving, and Christmas Day.
When you visit our websites, you can also limit our sharing with
social media, advertising, and analytics partners (some of which may constitute
CCPA "selling") by selecting your cookie preferences, which you can
access from the cookie banner on our websites or via the "Cookie
Settings" link at the bottom of the webpage.
Whether you use the web form or call us, we will need
information from you to process your CCPA sale opt-out request so that we can
confirm you are a California resident and determine if we have personal
information about you. We may also need to contact you about your request, and
you can choose the contact method you would like us to use.
Please be aware there might be circumstances where we will not
honor your sale opt-out request, as permitted under the CCPA. For example, if
we are not able to confirm that you are a California resident, we may not honor
your request.
You may designate, in writing or through a power of attorney, an
authorized agent to make a sale opt-out request on your behalf under the CCPA.
Before accepting such a request from an agent, we will require the agent to
provide proof you have authorized it to act on your behalf.
If you want an authorized agent to submit a “Do Not Sell My PI”
instruction on your behalf, the authorized agent must provide proof of your written
permission for the authorized agent to submit the instruction on your behalf.
Non-Discrimination.
You have the right not to be discriminated against for
exercising your right to opt out of CCPA “sales.”
7.
Changes
to This Privacy
Policy
We will update this Privacy
Policy when necessary to reflect changes in our products, services, or
features, how we use personal information, or the applicable law. When we post
changes to the Policy, we will change the date at the top of the Policy.
If we make material changes to the Policy, we will provide
notice or obtain consent regarding such changes as may be required by law.
This Privacy Policy is effective as of the date indicated at the
top of the Policy.
